30:55.757 --> 30:59.025
Ms. Shannon?

30:59.027 --> 31:00.694
Rosie.

31:00.696 --> 31:03.763
Are you okay?

31:03.765 --> 31:06.066
Why are you burning this book?

31:06.068 --> 31:08.568
'Cause I don't need it anymore.

31:12.708 --> 31:14.407
You knew.

31:14.409 --> 31:17.310
Excuse me?

31:17.312 --> 31:19.612
About Spence not being Tucker's father.

31:19.614 --> 31:23.750
That's why you didn't want Spence
to give blood for Tucker's surgery.

31:23.752 --> 31:28.221
- This is none of your business.
- It is my business!

31:28.223 --> 31:31.725
Spence is in jail while another
man should be.

31:31.727 --> 31:35.395
Ms. Shannon.

31:35.397 --> 31:38.298
I know you two weren't close,

31:38.300 --> 31:41.634
but your sister was murdered.

31:41.636 --> 31:43.169
Your sister.

31:43.171 --> 31:45.672
Why should I care about Peri?!

31:45.674 --> 31:50.176
All she ever did was rub her
success in my face.

31:50.178 --> 31:52.011
I'm sorry.

31:52.013 --> 31:55.148
But hiding the truth won't change that.

31:57.319 --> 32:00.453
I know about The Circle.

32:00.455 --> 32:03.156
I think they framed Spence to
protect the man

32:03.158 --> 32:05.158
Peri was having an affair with.

32:05.160 --> 32:08.361
Why would you help them cover
for your sister's murder?

32:08.363 --> 32:12.198
She wasn't having an affair.

32:12.200 --> 32:14.701
She was raped.

32:14.703 --> 32:16.836
What?

32:16.838 --> 32:19.706
I came over one day and found
her in tears.

32:19.708 --> 32:23.009
Some guy had drugged her and
had his way with her.

32:23.011 --> 32:24.310
Oh, my God.

32:24.312 --> 32:27.046
Nine months later, Tucker was born.

32:27.048 --> 32:29.716
Who was he, the man who raped her?

32:29.718 --> 32:31.785
She wouldn't tell me his name.

32:31.787 --> 32:35.755
Some bigwig in the movie business.

32:38.193 --> 32:39.526
[Sighs]

32:39.528 --> 32:41.561
[Footsteps on stairs] Ah!

32:41.563 --> 32:43.863
Sorry I took so long.

32:43.865 --> 32:46.466
Hope it was worth the wait.

32:46.468 --> 32:48.034
Mm.

32:51.039 --> 32:53.072
Something wrong?

32:53.074 --> 32:54.707
You tell me.

32:54.709 --> 32:57.977
When I left, we were in a
pretty big fight.

32:57.979 --> 32:59.879
Yeah, but we worked through
[chuckling] that.

32:59.881 --> 33:01.881
Didn't we?

33:01.883 --> 33:04.317
But we didn't talk for awhile,

33:04.319 --> 33:08.488
and sometimes things... happen.

33:08.490 --> 33:11.658
Peter, what are you saying?

33:11.660 --> 33:13.359
[Sighs]

33:13.361 --> 33:15.695
I just want to make sure we're good.

33:15.697 --> 33:17.997
We're good.

33:17.999 --> 33:21.334
We are really good.

33:23.104 --> 33:25.538
That's what I thought.

33:25.540 --> 33:27.707
Shall we? Mm.

33:30.212 --> 33:31.911
[Sighs]

33:39.721 --> 33:42.689
Carmen, I... [Gasps] Oh. Sorry.

33:42.691 --> 33:45.592
I was looking for you,
but you're crying.

33:45.594 --> 33:48.962
So now I'm torn because
I still need something ironed.

33:48.964 --> 33:50.897
I'll be right there. [Sniffles]

33:50.899 --> 33:53.566
All right.

33:53.568 --> 33:55.401
Well, what is it?

33:55.403 --> 33:57.604
Nothing.

33:57.606 --> 33:59.472
Carmen, I'm pretending
to be sympathetic.

33:59.474 --> 34:01.774
The least you could do is
pretend to appreciate it.

34:01.776 --> 34:06.246
A man that I knew a
long time ago, he...

34:06.248 --> 34:08.581
he died.

34:08.583 --> 34:11.117
Oh. Well...

34:11.119 --> 34:13.253
I'm sorry for your loss.

34:13.255 --> 34:16.222
It's stupid. I haven't
seen him in 20 years.

34:16.224 --> 34:17.924
[Sniffles]

34:17.926 --> 34:20.460
But it's the first man I ever loved.

34:22.330 --> 34:25.297
Probably the only man.

34:26.835 --> 34:29.402
I understand how you feel.

34:29.404 --> 34:31.737
You do?

34:31.739 --> 34:33.840
In a way.

34:33.842 --> 34:37.243
Adrian was my first and only love.

34:37.245 --> 34:39.445
And the night of the explosion,

34:39.447 --> 34:42.315
when I thought he'd died,
I was devastated.

34:42.317 --> 34:44.817
If you repeat this,
I will throttle you.

34:44.819 --> 34:47.085
I won't.

34:47.088 --> 34:48.788
[Sighs]

34:48.790 --> 34:50.956
As the house burned, I realized

34:50.958 --> 34:54.427
that the last thing I said to
him was that I hated him.

34:54.429 --> 34:57.030
Suddenly, the thought of a life
without him

34:57.032 --> 34:58.865
was more than I could bear.

34:58.867 --> 35:01.334
That must've been hard.

35:01.336 --> 35:03.937
I think I was just afraid

35:03.939 --> 35:07.774
that I would never find anyone else.

35:07.776 --> 35:10.009
But I was wrong.

35:10.011 --> 35:13.846
It is hard to imagine when the
loss is fresh,

35:13.848 --> 35:15.949
but you will love again.

35:15.951 --> 35:19.152
Thanks.
[Exhales sharply]

35:19.154 --> 35:21.788
Of course it helps if your first love

35:21.790 --> 35:25.291
turns out to be a
real son of a bitch.

35:25.293 --> 35:28.361
[Chuckles]

35:31.366 --> 35:34.801
I need you to see what you
could find out about this man,

35:34.803 --> 35:36.703
the Reverend James Hamilton.

35:36.705 --> 35:39.238
Why are you digging in to this guy?

35:39.240 --> 35:42.742
My wife believes he's the greatest man
that ever walked the Earth.

35:42.744 --> 35:44.310
I intend to prove her wrong.

35:44.312 --> 35:46.212
And you think he's up to no good?

35:46.214 --> 35:47.647
He's a man of God.

35:47.649 --> 35:50.516
There must be a few skeletons
in his closet.

35:51.820 --> 35:55.555
I need to know what he's hiding.

35:57.177 --> 35:58.543
[Doorbell rings]

36:00.110 --> 36:01.742
Is Peter here?

36:01.777 --> 36:03.262
No.

36:03.335 --> 36:05.502
But, listen, Jesse, you can't
keep showing up here like this.

36:05.504 --> 36:08.505
Just hear me out. It's important.

36:08.507 --> 36:09.806
Okay.

36:13.445 --> 36:14.711
[Door closes]

36:14.713 --> 36:16.613
Look, I told Daniela

36:16.615 --> 36:18.148
I slept with someone while she
was gone.

36:18.150 --> 36:21.184
Don't worry. I didn't
mention your name.

36:21.186 --> 36:22.886
How'd she take it?

36:22.888 --> 36:26.056
That's the weird thing.
It didn't bother her at all.

36:26.058 --> 36:28.358
- Well, that should be a relief.
- It's not.

36:28.360 --> 36:30.160
If you really care about someone,

36:30.162 --> 36:32.496
it bothers you when they're
with someone else.

36:32.498 --> 36:34.197
I agree.

36:34.199 --> 36:38.168
Just like it bothers me that
you're with someone else.

36:38.170 --> 36:40.370
Jesse.

36:40.372 --> 36:42.973
I should have never broken up
with you.

36:42.975 --> 36:44.741
I realize that now.

36:44.743 --> 36:47.310
What we had...

36:47.312 --> 36:48.945
that's what I want.

36:51.750 --> 36:53.717
No. No, no.

36:53.719 --> 36:56.086
Marisol, you have feelings for me.

36:56.088 --> 36:57.921
- You can't deny that.
- Look.

36:57.923 --> 36:59.322
[Exhales sharply]

36:59.324 --> 37:01.525
The last thing I want to do is
hurt you,

37:01.527 --> 37:05.529
but I am with Peter now.
You have to accept that.

37:05.531 --> 37:08.098
I'm sorry, Jesse.

37:08.100 --> 37:11.268
Well...

37:11.270 --> 37:14.838
I had to give it a shot.

37:14.840 --> 37:15.806
[Sighs]

37:17.443 --> 37:18.975
Bye, Marisol.

37:26.785 --> 37:28.418
[Door closes]

37:36.595 --> 37:39.963
[Cellphone beeps, line ringing]

37:39.965 --> 37:41.965
[Sighs] Well?

37:41.967 --> 37:44.868
You were right.
Marisol's seeing her ex again.

37:44.870 --> 37:46.803
Thanks.

37:46.805 --> 37:48.338
[Cellphone beeps]

37:54.813 --> 37:56.580
[Yells]

37:56.582 --> 37:58.081
[Clatter]

38:05.257 --> 38:07.324
If you keep cleaning at night
like this,

38:07.326 --> 38:09.559
you're gonna make me look bad.
[Chuckles]

38:09.561 --> 38:12.763
You just stay on your side,
and I'll stay on mine.

38:14.099 --> 38:15.565
Danni.

38:15.567 --> 38:18.168
I know you don't want to talk to me,

38:18.170 --> 38:21.138
but there are some things that
I need to tell you.

38:21.140 --> 38:22.515
Like what?

38:24.132 --> 38:27.277
Your father, Lucas.

38:27.279 --> 38:32.082
He was the best man I ever
knew, and I loved him so much.

38:32.084 --> 38:35.952
And I know he would have married me
if I told him that I was pregnant.

38:35.954 --> 38:37.654
Then why didn't you tell him?

38:37.656 --> 38:40.624
Because I wanted to be a star.

38:40.626 --> 38:43.493
And I knew that having a
husband and a baby

38:43.495 --> 38:46.163
was gonna make it harder for me.

38:46.165 --> 38:49.099
Giving you up was the right
thing, Danni.

38:49.101 --> 38:51.535
And I know it was selfish, but...

38:51.537 --> 38:53.503
it's what I did.

38:53.505 --> 38:54.771
Great.

38:54.773 --> 38:57.474
Now I know. Is that it?

39:00.179 --> 39:02.145
Here.

39:02.147 --> 39:04.981
This belonged to your father.

39:04.983 --> 39:07.751
I know he would have loved for
you to have it.

39:17.629 --> 39:19.496
Thanks.

39:35.414 --> 39:38.248
Lucas? It's me.

39:38.250 --> 39:41.184
Listen, I don't think
you should come here.

39:41.186 --> 39:43.253
Sorry. I tried.

39:43.255 --> 39:45.822
But Carmen doesn't want to see you.

39:49.895 --> 39:52.996
So? Everything okay up here?

39:52.998 --> 39:54.364
Yeah, I don't see any damage.

39:54.366 --> 39:55.732
Oh, good.

39:55.734 --> 39:57.367
I'm so glad you're home

39:57.369 --> 40:00.070
to help me with these sorts of
things.

40:00.072 --> 40:02.239
I admit...

40:02.241 --> 40:05.041
I was lost without you.

40:05.043 --> 40:08.011
The Circle just didn't feel complete.

40:08.013 --> 40:10.447
About The Circle...

40:10.449 --> 40:13.750
I'm not gonna be involved anymore.

40:15.502 --> 40:17.454
Kyle, I'm sorry,

40:17.456 --> 40:21.258
but you're already involved
more than you know.

40:21.260 --> 40:24.861
You see, there's something else
I need you to take care of.

40:33.438 --> 40:35.038
Ben?

40:35.040 --> 40:38.742
Be a good boy and get rid of
this for me, okay?

40:39.978 --> 40:41.912
Rosie, that's horrible.

40:41.914 --> 40:46.082
I know, but I think the man who
raped Peri could be the killer.

40:46.084 --> 40:47.317
But you don't know who he is.

40:47.319 --> 40:48.585
<i>Mnh-mnh.</i>

40:48.587 --> 40:50.320
That's why I still need to find

40:50.322 --> 40:52.956
the video of Peri confessing
her secret.

40:52.958 --> 40:55.125
Maybe she said who the man was.

40:55.127 --> 40:56.893
Well, I noticed Kyle and his mom

40:56.895 --> 40:58.962
being really secretive about
the attic.

40:58.964 --> 41:01.164
It's like they don't want
anybody up there.

41:01.166 --> 41:03.833
Maybe that's where the cult meets...

41:03.835 --> 41:06.002
and where they keep the videos.

41:06.004 --> 41:10.473
So, maybe I can drum up some reason
to sneak in there and snoop around.

41:10.475 --> 41:14.144
We're going to get Spence
out of jail. I can feel it.

41:14.146 --> 41:15.679
[Door opens]

41:15.681 --> 41:17.314
Sorry, I got to call you back.

41:17.316 --> 41:20.183
Hello?

41:20.185 --> 41:22.419
Ooh! Sorry, I didn't
mean to startle you.

41:22.421 --> 41:24.020
I'm Fiona.

41:24.022 --> 41:26.156
Fiona!

41:26.158 --> 41:29.926
Oh, my God! I thought
you were... in Italy.

41:29.928 --> 41:31.294
Well, I'm back early.

41:31.296 --> 41:34.798
You must be Zoila, my maid.

